            NAME 
            make.legend - Generates a cultural and/or thematic legend
            for the map composition.
            
            SYNOPSIS 
            make.legend [filename]
            
            DESCRIPTION 
            make.legend constructs a single column cultural and/or 
            thematic legend for the map composition.  The
            characteristics of the legend boxes are defined during the
            command input session.  Legend text for cultural features,
            using linear and point symbols (i.e. roads, drains), and for
            thematic area fills are identified by their file names as
            input for the legend.  The make.legend command should not be 
            issued until all contents of the map composition have been
            generated.  If given, [filename] is used for the name of the
            overlay file generated.  Multiple legend files may be
            generated for the map composition by using unique overlay
            file names.
            
            The user is required to provide the following:
            
                 - map definition file name
                 - overlay file name (if not specified in the command
                      line)
                 - plotter pen number
                 - text font
                 - text size
                 - text leading
                 - relationship of the text to a window within the
                      map composition
                 - location of the first legend entry
                 - horizontal distance between the legend symbol/box
                      and the text
                 - horizontal and vertical size of the legend boxes
                 - fill, symbol and line files to include
            
            Completing the response sequence generates the required
            files to construct the map element.  Definition parameters
            are stored in the legend/par directory; graphic elements to 
            draw the map on the screen or plotter are stored in the ovm
            directory.  The default file name for both directories is
            legend. 
            
            Changing the appearance of the legend (e.g. position, text
            size, box size, etc.) can be done by regenerating the
            make.legend command and overwriting the initial file, or by


