                 (edit) example:          vi misc/[filename]
                                          vi misc/legend/par/legend 
            
            EXAMPLE
            The file legend/par/legend will construct four legend boxes
            on the map compilation beginning at 43 cm over in x and
            12.75 cm up in y from the lower left corner of the plotting
            window.  The legend boxes will be drawn 1 cm wide and 1/2 cm
            high, with the legend text beginning .25 cm to the right of
            the legend box outline.  The default text font -sr has been
            used.  The fill colors and patterns in the boxes will
            duplicate the results of the four thematic fills produced by
            using the make.fill command.
  
            
                 PEN=1
                 FONT=               # default font (-sr)
                 CHAR_SIZE=0.250     
                 window=p            # plot window
                 x=43.000
                 x_offset=0.250      # distance between pattern and text
                 y=12.750
                 y_offset=0.250      # distance between boxes
                 h_size=1.000        # horizontal box size
                 v_size=0.500        # vertical box size
                 fillname=unix       # legend entry
                 fillname=dos
                 fillname=none
                 fillname=not
                 fillname=.          # end legend entries
            
            NOTE 
            If only one map element will be drawn on the map
            composition, the default selection for the file name is
            recommended for use.
            
            The delete key will abort the make.legend command.
            
